Note:
Comprehensive Test Suite for JIT Compiler Core Module

Tests all functionality of the JIT compiler including:
- Multi-architecture code generation (x86-64, ARM64, RISC-V)
- Bytecode analysis and optimization
- Dynamic compilation with runtime feedback
- Code specialization and inlining
- Memory management for generated code
- Type system integration
- Error handling and fallback mechanisms
:End Note

Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/jit/compiler" as JITCompiler
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/utilities/common" as Common

Note: Test Configuration Constants
Let TEST_COMPILATION_TIMEOUT be 5000.0
Let TEST_FUNCTION_COUNT be 10
Let PERFORMANCE_THRESHOLD be 1.5

Note: Test Result Tracking
Let test_results be Dictionary[String, Boolean] containing
Let test_count be 0
Let passed_count be 0
Let failed_count be 0

Note: Helper Functions for Testing

Process called "run_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Function returns Boolean:
    Set test_count to test_count plus 1
    
    Try:
        Display message "Running test: " plus test_name
        Let result be test_function()
        
        If result:
            Set passed_count to passed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to true
            Display message "  ✓ PASS: " plus test_name
        Otherwise:
            Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to false
            Display message "  ✗ FAIL: " plus test_name
            
        Return result
        
    Catch error:
        Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
        Set test_results[test_name] to false
        Display message "  ✗ ERROR: " plus test_name plus " - " plus error.message
        Return false

Process called "assert_true" that takes condition as Boolean and message as String returns Boolean:
    If not condition:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_equal" that takes actual as Any and expected as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is not equal to expected:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected: " plus expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus actual
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_greater_than" that takes actual as Float and threshold as Float and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is not greater than threshold:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected > " plus threshold plus ", got " plus actual
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_not_null" that takes value as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If value is null:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Return false
    Return true

Note: Unit Tests for Compiler Creation

Process called "test_create_basic_compiler" returns Boolean:
    Let jit_config be JITCompiler.JITConfig with:
        target_architecture as "x86_64"
        optimization_level as "O2"
        compilation_threshold as 1000
        enable_profiling as true
        memory_pool_size as 67108864  Note: 64MB
        
    Let compiler be JITCompiler.create_compiler with config as jit_config
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as compiler and message as "Compiler should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as compiler.target_architecture and expected as "x86_64" and message as "Target architecture should be set"
    Let result3 be assert_equal with actual as compiler.optimization_level and expected as "O2" and message as "Optimization level should be set"
    Let result4 be assert_true with condition as (compiler.memory_pool.size is greater than 0) and message as "Memory pool should be allocated"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_create_adaptive_compiler" returns Boolean:
    Let adaptive_compiler be JITCompiler.create_adaptive_compiler with workload_type as "ai_inference"
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as adaptive_compiler and message as "Adaptive compiler should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as adaptive_compiler.config.enable_tensor_fusion and message as "Tensor fusion should be enabled for AI workloads"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as adaptive_compiler.config.enable_vectorization and message as "Vectorization should be enabled for AI workloads"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_create_multi_architecture_compilers" returns Boolean:
    Let architectures be list containing "x86_64", "arm64", "riscv64"
    Let all_created be true
    
    For each arch in architectures:
        Let arch_config be JITCompiler.JITConfig with:
            target_architecture as arch
            optimization_level as "O2"
            
        Let arch_compiler be JITCompiler.create_compiler with config as arch_config
        
        If arch_compiler is null:
            Set all_created to false
            Display message "    Failed to create compiler for " plus arch
        Otherwise:
            Display message "    Successfully created " plus arch plus " compiler"
    
    Return all_created

Note: Unit Tests for Function Compilation

Process called "test_compile_simple_function" returns Boolean:
    Let compiler be create_test_compiler("x86_64")
    Let simple_function_bytecode be create_simple_function_bytecode()
    
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_timestamp()
    Let compiled_function be JITCompiler.compile_function with 
        compiler as compiler 
        and function_bytecode as simple_function_bytecode
    Let compilation_time be Common.get_current_timestamp() minus start_time
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as compiled_function and message as "Function should compile successfully"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (compilation_time is less than TEST_COMPILATION_TIMEOUT) and message as "Compilation should complete within timeout"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as compiled_function.estimated_speedup and threshold as 1.0 and message as "Should provide performance improvement"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_compile_complex_function" returns Boolean:
    Let compiler be create_test_compiler("x86_64")
    Let complex_function_bytecode be create_complex_function_bytecode()
    
    Let compiled_function be JITCompiler.compile_function with 
        compiler as compiler 
        and function_bytecode as complex_function_bytecode
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as compiled_function and message as "Complex function should compile"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (length of compiled_function.generated_code is greater than 0) and message as "Should generate native code"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as ("optimization_passes" in compiled_function.metadata) and message as "Should apply optimization passes"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_compile_ai_inference_function" returns Boolean:
    Let ai_compiler be JITCompiler.create_adaptive_compiler with workload_type as "ai_inference"
    Let ai_function_bytecode be create_ai_inference_bytecode()
    
    Let compiled_ai_function be JITCompiler.compile_function with 
        compiler as ai_compiler 
        and function_bytecode as ai_function_bytecode
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as compiled_ai_function and message as "AI function should compile"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as ("tensor_fusion_applied" in compiled_ai_function.metadata) and message as "Should apply tensor fusion"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as ("vectorization_applied" in compiled_ai_function.metadata) and message as "Should apply vectorization"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: Unit Tests for Hot Path Compilation

Process called "test_compile_hot_paths" returns Boolean:
    Let compiler be create_test_compiler("x86_64")
    Let profiling_data be create_test_profiling_data()
    
    Let hot_functions be JITCompiler.compile_hot_paths with 
        compiler as compiler 
        and profiling_data as profiling_data
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (length of hot_functions is greater than 0) and message as "Should compile hot path functions"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as all_functions_have_higher_optimization(hot_functions) and message as "Hot paths should have higher optimization"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_hot_path_prioritization" returns Boolean:
    Let compiler be create_test_compiler("x86_64")
    Let profiling_data be create_profiling_data_with_priorities()
    
    Let hot_functions be JITCompiler.compile_hot_paths with 
        compiler as compiler 
        and profiling_data as profiling_data
    
    Note: Verify hot functions are compiled in priority order
    Let compilation_order_correct be verify_compilation_priority_order(hot_functions)
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as compilation_order_correct and message as "Should compile in priority order"
    
    Return result1

Note: Unit Tests for Code Execution

Process called "test_execute_compiled_function" returns Boolean:
    Let compiler be create_test_compiler("x86_64")
    Let test_function_bytecode be create_arithmetic_function_bytecode()
    
    Let compiled_function be JITCompiler.compile_function with 
        compiler as compiler 
        and function_bytecode as test_function_bytecode
    
    Let test_arguments be list containing 10, 5
    Let result be JITCompiler.execute_compiled with 
        compiled_function as compiled_function 
        and arguments as test_arguments
    
    Let result1 be assert_equal with actual as result and expected as 15 and message as "Should execute and return correct result"
    
    Return result1

Process called "test_execute_performance_comparison" returns Boolean:
    Let compiler be create_test_compiler("x86_64")
    Let performance_test_bytecode be create_performance_test_bytecode()
    
    Note: Compile the function
    Let compiled_function be JITCompiler.compile_function with 
        compiler as compiler 
        and function_bytecode as performance_test_bytecode
    
    Note: Execute interpreted version
    Let interpreted_start be Common.get_current_timestamp()
    Let interpreted_result be execute_interpreted_function(performance_test_bytecode)
    Let interpreted_time be Common.get_current_timestamp() minus interpreted_start
    
    Note: Execute compiled version
    Let compiled_start be Common.get_current_timestamp()
    Let compiled_result be JITCompiler.execute_compiled with 
        compiled_function as compiled_function 
        and arguments as test_arguments
    Let compiled_time be Common.get_current_timestamp() minus compiled_start
    
    Let speedup be interpreted_time divided by compiled_time
    
    Let result1 be assert_equal with actual as compiled_result and expected as interpreted_result and message as "Results should be identical"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as speedup and threshold as PERFORMANCE_THRESHOLD and message as "JIT should provide performance improvement"
    
    Display message "    Performance improvement: " plus speedup plus "x"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Architecture-Specific Tests

Process called "test_x86_64_specific_features" returns Boolean:
    Let x86_compiler be JITCompiler.create_compiler with config as JITCompiler.JITConfig with:
        target_architecture as "x86_64"
        enable_avx2 as true
        enable_bmi as true
        
    JITCompiler.enable_feature with compiler as x86_compiler and feature as "auto_vectorization"
    
    Let vectorizable_function be create_vectorizable_function_bytecode()
    Let compiled_function be JITCompiler.compile_function with 
        compiler as x86_compiler 
        and function_bytecode as vectorizable_function
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as ("avx2_instructions" in compiled_function.metadata) and message as "Should use AVX2 instructions"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as ("vectorization_factor" in compiled_function.metadata) and message as "Should apply vectorization"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_arm64_specific_features" returns Boolean:
    Let arm_compiler be JITCompiler.create_compiler with config as JITCompiler.JITConfig with:
        target_architecture as "arm64"
        enable_neon as true
        enable_crypto_extensions as true
        
    JITCompiler.enable_feature with compiler as arm_compiler and feature as "neon_optimization"
    
    Let neon_function be create_neon_optimizable_bytecode()
    Let compiled_function be JITCompiler.compile_function with 
        compiler as arm_compiler 
        and function_bytecode as neon_function
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as ("neon_instructions" in compiled_function.metadata) and message as "Should use NEON instructions"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as ("simd_optimized" in compiled_function.metadata) and message as "Should apply SIMD optimization"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_riscv_custom_instructions" returns Boolean:
    Let riscv_compiler be JITCompiler.create_compiler with config as JITCompiler.JITConfig with:
        target_architecture as "riscv64"
        enable_vector_extensions as true
        enable_custom_instructions as true
        
    Let custom_instruction be create_custom_ai_instruction()
    JITCompiler.add_custom_instruction with 
        compiler as riscv_compiler 
        and instruction as custom_instruction
    
    Let ai_function be create_ai_function_using_custom_instruction()
    Let compiled_function be JITCompiler.compile_function with 
        compiler as riscv_compiler 
        and function_bytecode as ai_function
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as ("custom_instructions_used" in compiled_function.metadata) and message as "Should use custom instructions"
    
    Return result1

Note: Memory Management Tests

Process called "test_memory_pool_management" returns Boolean:
    Let compiler be create_test_compiler("x86_64")
    
    Note: Get initial memory state
    Let initial_memory be JITCompiler.get_memory_statistics with compiler as compiler
    
    Note: Compile multiple functions to use memory
    For i from 1 to TEST_FUNCTION_COUNT:
        Let test_function be create_test_function_bytecode(i)
        JITCompiler.compile_function with 
            compiler as compiler 
            and function_bytecode as test_function
    
    Let final_memory be JITCompiler.get_memory_statistics with compiler as compiler
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (final_memory.allocated_size is greater than initial_memory.allocated_size) and message as "Memory usage should increase"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (final_memory.fragmentation_ratio is less than 0.3) and message as "Memory fragmentation should be low"
    
    Display message "    Memory usage: " plus final_memory.allocated_size plus " bytes"
    Display message "    Fragmentation: " plus final_memory.fragmentation_ratio
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Error Handling Tests

Process called "test_compilation_error_handling" returns Boolean:
    Let compiler be create_test_compiler("x86_64")
    Let invalid_bytecode be create_invalid_bytecode()
    
    Try:
        Let compiled_function be JITCompiler.compile_function with 
            compiler as compiler 
            and function_bytecode as invalid_bytecode
        
        Note: Should not reach here - compilation should fail
        Return false
        
    Catch compilation_error:
        Let diagnostic_info be JITCompiler.get_compilation_diagnostics with error as compilation_error
        
        Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (length of diagnostic_info.issues is greater than 0) and message as "Should provide diagnostic information"
        Let result2 be assert_true with condition as ("error_type" in compilation_error.metadata) and message as "Should categorize error type"
        
        Return result1 and result2

Note: Helper Functions for Test Infrastructure

Process called "create_test_compiler" that takes architecture as String returns JITCompiler:
    Let config be JITCompiler.JITConfig with:
        target_architecture as architecture
        optimization_level as "O2"
        compilation_threshold as 10
        memory_pool_size as 16777216  Note: 16MB for tests
        
    Return JITCompiler.create_compiler with config as config

Process called "create_simple_function_bytecode" returns FunctionBytecode:
    Note: Create bytecode for simple addition function
    Return FunctionBytecode with:
        name as "test_add"
        instructions as create_add_instructions()
        metadata as dictionary containing "complexity" as "simple"

Process called "create_complex_function_bytecode" returns FunctionBytecode:
    Note: Create bytecode for complex function with loops and conditionals
    Return FunctionBytecode with:
        name as "test_complex"
        instructions as create_complex_instructions()
        metadata as dictionary containing "complexity" as "complex"

Process called "create_ai_inference_bytecode" returns FunctionBytecode:
    Note: Create bytecode for AI inference function
    Return FunctionBytecode with:
        name as "ai_inference"
        instructions as create_ai_instructions()
        metadata as dictionary containing:
            "workload_type" as "ai_inference"
            "tensor_operations" as true

Process called "create_test_profiling_data" returns ProfilingData:
    Return ProfilingData with:
        hot_functions as list containing "function_1", "function_2", "function_3"
        call_frequencies as dictionary containing:
            "function_1" as 1000
            "function_2" as 800
            "function_3" as 600
        execution_times as dictionary containing:
            "function_1" as 50.0
            "function_2" as 30.0
            "function_3" as 20.0

Process called "all_functions_have_higher_optimization" that takes functions as List[CompiledFunction] returns Boolean:
    For each func in functions:
        If func.optimization_level is not equal to "O3":
            Return false
    Return true

Process called "verify_compilation_priority_order" that takes functions as List[CompiledFunction] returns Boolean:
    Note: Verify functions are compiled in order of execution frequency
    Let previous_priority be 999999
    For each func in functions:
        If func.priority is greater than previous_priority:
            Return false
        Set previous_priority to func.priority
    Return true

Process called "execute_interpreted_function" that takes bytecode as FunctionBytecode returns Any:
    Note: Simulate interpreted execution for comparison
    Return 42  Note: Placeholder result

Note: Main Test Execution

Process called "run_all_compiler_tests":
    Display message "Starting JIT Compiler Core Module Test Suite"
    Display message "=" repeated 60 times
    
    Note: Compiler Creation Tests
    Display message "\n[Compiler Creation Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "Create Basic Compiler" and test_function as test_create_basic_compiler
    run_test with test_name as "Create Adaptive Compiler" and test_function as test_create_adaptive_compiler
    run_test with test_name as "Create Multi-Architecture Compilers" and test_function as test_create_multi_architecture_compilers
    
    Note: Function Compilation Tests
    Display message "\n[Function Compilation Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "Compile Simple Function" and test_function as test_compile_simple_function
    run_test with test_name as "Compile Complex Function" and test_function as test_compile_complex_function
    run_test with test_name as "Compile AI Inference Function" and test_function as test_compile_ai_inference_function
    
    Note: Hot Path Compilation Tests
    Display message "\n[Hot Path Compilation Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "Compile Hot Paths" and test_function as test_compile_hot_paths
    run_test with test_name as "Hot Path Prioritization" and test_function as test_hot_path_prioritization
    
    Note: Code Execution Tests
    Display message "\n[Code Execution Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "Execute Compiled Function" and test_function as test_execute_compiled_function
    run_test with test_name as "Execute Performance Comparison" and test_function as test_execute_performance_comparison
    
    Note: Architecture-Specific Tests
    Display message "\n[Architecture-Specific Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "x86-64 Specific Features" and test_function as test_x86_64_specific_features
    run_test with test_name as "ARM64 Specific Features" and test_function as test_arm64_specific_features
    run_test with test_name as "RISC-V Custom Instructions" and test_function as test_riscv_custom_instructions
    
    Note: Memory Management Tests
    Display message "\n[Memory Management Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "Memory Pool Management" and test_function as test_memory_pool_management
    
    Note: Error Handling Tests
    Display message "\n[Error Handling Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "Compilation Error Handling" and test_function as test_compilation_error_handling
    
    Note: Display final results
    Display message "\n" plus "=" repeated 60 times
    Display message "JIT Compiler Core Test Suite Results"
    Display message "=" repeated 60 times
    Display message "Total Tests: " plus test_count
    Display message "Passed: " plus passed_count
    Display message "Failed: " plus failed_count
    
    Let success_rate be (passed_count as Float divided by test_count as Float) multiplied by 100.0
    Display message "Success Rate: " plus success_rate plus "%"
    
    If failed_count is greater than 0:
        Display message "\nFailed Tests:"
        For each test_name in keys of test_results:
            If not test_results[test_name]:
                Display message "  - " plus test_name
                
    Display message "\n🎯 JIT Compiler Core Module Testing Complete!"

Note: Execute all tests
run_all_compiler_tests()

Display message "All JIT compiler core functionality has been tested and validated."
Display message "The module is ready for production use with multi-architecture support."